The paper is related to speech enhancement using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SD). The paper also involves the use of auxiliary structures and joint optimization, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ideal binary masks, which are commonly used in speech separation and source separation (cs.SI).
